title: >>> The BUNKER
body_text:
Before this huge event, DODGEBALL XXVIII, one perhaps would like to enjoy dodgeball a little differently. What better way than with a dodgeball word search!
Word Search Fact: This was made the week of DODGEBALL 23.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
DODGEBALL 29, one step closer to "Homecoming", is already making history before its arrival! As announced last week, Justin Pierce will go one-on-one with Dan Spengeman in an "Ultimate Poster Contest". Both men have won respective poster contests: Justin for DODGEBALL 17 and Dan for DODGEBALL TWENTY-SIX.
Other works can be seen for such events like:
DODGEBALL XIV (Created by Justin)
DODGEBALL 18 and 19 (Created by Dan)
DODGEBALL 21 (Created by Dan)
(Take a look!
http://community.webshots.com/user/undertaker15yrs
)
Looking at their past contributions, it will be a fun contest all can enjoy. Their talents will show once again in this "Ultimate" DODGEBALL 29 match-up.
RULES: Both Justin and Dan submit two posters each [anonymously please]. From there, you the audience, will decide which of the four possible posters becomes DODGEBALL 29's logo.
Good luck to both contestants!
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
DODGEBALL 30, already sending the sport into a frenzy, will easily be one of the biggest events ever.
Sunday, March 12th, 2006
Special start time: 2PM
Location: Ocean Road Park
However, more news concerning this milestone event has been released.
DODGEBALL X: Staind "Mudshovel"
DODGEBALL 20: Filter "Hey Man, Nice Shot"
See where this is all going? If you guessed the theme song, you are right on. DODGEBALL 30 has hit the jackpot with an outstanding song, Van Halen's "Right Now".
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Another classic night is upon us ...
